{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:06.043Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase state. Let me review the Step 3 plan.\n\n## Plan Review: Step 3 — Build Components\n\n### Verdict: APPROVE\n\n### Summary\nThe plan is well-structured and detailed enough to implement three Astro components (`ReleaseCard`, `StreamingLinks`, `TrackList`) that will correctly render the release content collection data. The schema and sample content","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:08.377Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":" are already in place from Steps 1–2, and all props interfaces are clearly specified. The step will achieve its outcomes.\n\n### Issues Found\n1. **[Severity: minor]** — The `TrackList` component spec says rows \"on hover, show a small 'play' icon on the left (where the track number was) to indicate clickability\" but also says \"rows are non-interactive.\" This is","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:10.330Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":" purely visual and implementable with CSS (`group-hover` swapping a number for an SVG), but the worker should be aware these are contradictory statements — the hover state implies clickability that doesn't exist yet. Not blocking since the spec explicitly acknowledges KB-003 will handle actual playback.\n\n2. **[Severity: minor]** — The `ReleaseCard` spec says \"Props: `release` (full release collection entry)\" but","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:12.628Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":" with Astro 5's `glob()` loader, the collection entry type is `CollectionEntry<'releases'>`. The worker needs to know the correct import path — `type { CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content'` — to get proper type annotations. This is standard Astro but worth noting since the codebase uses Astro 5 content layer API rather than the legacy content collections.\n\n### Suggestions\n- **StreamingLinks icon","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:15.434Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":" sourcing:** The spec says \"use inline SVG icons — no external dependency\" for Spotify, Apple Music, YouTube Music, and Bandcamp. The worker should plan to embed small SVG path data directly in the component. Simple Icons (simpleicons.org) is a good reference for accurate brand SVG paths, but they should be hand-inlined rather than npm-installed. This is well within scope.\n- **ReleaseCard `showType","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:17.902Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":"` prop:** The spec includes `showType?: boolean` defaulting to `true`. The listing page (Step 4) groups releases by type with section headings, so cards within a section would have redundant type badges. Consider whether `showType` will default to `false` in grouped contexts — the prop exists for exactly this reason, which is good design.\n- **Accessibility:** Consider adding `alt` text to the","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:19.283Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":" album art images in `ReleaseCard` using the release title (e.g., `alt=\"{title} album artwork\"`). The spec doesn't mention this explicitly but it's standard practice.\n- **TrackList external link icon:** The spec says \"if a track has streaming URLs, show a small external link icon on the right side.\" With 4 possible streaming platforms per track, the worker should decide whether to show one generic","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:06:19.663Z","taskId":"KB-004","text":" icon or per-platform icons. A single generic external-link icon is simpler and sufficient for the detail page where `StreamingLinks` already shows platform-specific links above.","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
